1
00:00:01,390 --> 00:00:02,390
From now on,

2
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:05,200
you only get to be like this with me.

3
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:07,760
Got it?

4
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,200
Zen...

5
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:15,760
I...

6
00:00:15,761 --> 00:00:17,720
You didn't actually think
I'd say that, did you?

7
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:18,790
Idiot.

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,600
See ya.

9
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:38,900
"Fake Fact Lips"

10
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,771
(Episode 3: Didn't I tell you?
You only have eyes for me.)

11
00:01:41,795 --> 00:01:43,866
For the next product, I'm
thinking of a pre-launch strategy

12
00:01:43,890 --> 00:01:48,170
where we intentionally keep
the full design under wraps.

13
00:01:48,330 --> 00:01:50,760
This should help build
some real anticipation.

14
00:01:51,170 --> 00:01:51,720
For example,

15
00:01:51,721 --> 00:01:56,750
we could release close-up shots of the
packaging or silhouette videos every week.

16
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:10,660
You were out like a light.

17
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,389
By doing this,

18
00:02:13,390 --> 00:02:16,350
we expect social media
traffic to increase by 10%.

19
00:02:17,650 --> 00:02:18,650
What do you think?

20
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:22,630
Shido-san?

21
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:24,800
Huh?

22
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Oh.

23
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:27,890
Um...

24
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:30,950
What was that again?

25
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:32,429
I knew you weren't listening.

26
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:33,490
No, I was listening.

27
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,100
Uh...

28
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:36,390
Good grief...

29
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:38,060
Never mind.

30
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,320
Sorry.

31
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:43,400
Hey, Shido-san.

32
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,249
Is something going on
between you and Yotsuya-san?

33
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:47,430
Yotsuya?!

34
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:49,310
Why do you ask?

35
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:50,800
No, just a feeling.

36
00:02:51,270 --> 00:02:54,280
The vibe between you
two has been a bit off lately.

37
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:55,450
It's nothing.

38
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:56,670
Nothing at all.

39
00:02:58,390 --> 00:02:59,390
Oh.

40
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:02,300
(Incoming call: Yotsuya Ryo)

41
00:03:02,370 --> 00:03:03,370
Oh?

42
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:12,420
What do you want?

43
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:15,680
You left your tie at my place yesterday.

44
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,500
Is that it?

45
00:03:17,990 --> 00:03:20,300
You could've just brought
it to the office quietly.

46
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:21,850
What?

47
00:03:22,460 --> 00:03:24,660
So you didn't leave it on purpose?

48
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,580
Huh? Why would I do that?

49
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:31,540
You're really clumsy at playing mind games.

50
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,150
I'm hanging up.

51
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:36,060
Hey, Zen...

52
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,720
What?

53
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,400
Don't forget, this is a competition.

54
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:44,000
At this rate,

55
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,140
it's becoming a game where
I'm the one winning you over.

56
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,830
Then bring it to the office now.

57
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:53,060
Can't, I'm out right now.

58
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:54,940
Yotsuya-san!

59
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:56,610
Coming!

60
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:58,920
Uh, gotta go.

61
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:02,030
We'll talk about the tie later.

62
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:08,359
I heard a new Genghis Khan
BBQ place opened by the station.

63
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,730
Want to go?

64
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:14,570
Come on, Senpai, let's go!

65
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,740
What did Yotsuya-san want?

66
00:04:17,150 --> 00:04:18,250
What was it again?

67
00:04:19,030 --> 00:04:20,030
Forgot.

68
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:23,480
Please, just try to get along.

69
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:24,960
Ah.

70
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,440
We're about to head out.

71
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,440
Want to grab a drink?

72
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,560
Oh, I have to make an
appearance at a client's party.

73
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,350
A party?

74
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,780
It's not for fun, it's work.

75
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,640
Networking is important, I guess.

76
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,420
Let's do it another time.

77
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:41,409
- We're heading out.
- Excuse us.

78
00:04:41,410 --> 00:04:42,480
Yeah, see you tomorrow.

79
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,220
Let's go.

80
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,240
You're impossible.

81
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,760
That place is amazing.

82
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,270
President Shii, you inherited
the winery at such a young age.

83
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,000
Has your mindset changed at all?

84
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,130
My mindset hasn't changed.

85
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,070
The mission to create even
better, more beloved wines,

86
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,350
that sense of mission,

87
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:02,896
and the sense of responsibility,
I've always kept them in mind.

88
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,410
Is the adoption of "night harvesting" also

89
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:08,440
part of your commitment to higher quality?

90
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,920
Exactly.

91
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,710
- Shido-kun!
- Shimizu-san.

92
00:05:15,110 --> 00:05:16,110
Long time no see.

93
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,040
- You're looking sharp.
- Oh, please, don't say that.

94
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:21,240
- Let's catch up again.
- Definitely.

95
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,919
Oh, Shido-san.

96
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,920
Oh, good work.

97
00:05:23,921 --> 00:05:26,579
- Thank you for your continued support.
- No, thank you for yours.

98
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:28,879
- I look forward to working with you.
- Likewise.

99
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,880
Excuse me.

100
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,810
Shido-san, good work.

101
00:05:32,890 --> 00:05:34,190
Oh, good work...

102
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,660
Yeah, Ryo... Yotsuya?!

103
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:37,800
What's with the "Ryo Yotsuya"?

104
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:39,550
What are you doing here?

105
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:41,800
No, that's my line.

106
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:45,270
- Mochida, long time no see.
- Yotsuya! Long time no see!

107
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,920
Oh, Shido-san!

108
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:49,620
- Thanks for coming.
- Good work.

109
00:05:49,644 --> 00:05:50,644
Good work.

110
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:51,710
Hm?
Huh?

111
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,230
You two know each other?!

112
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,480
Wow, you said that in unison.

113
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:00,950
Huh?

114
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:03,280
- Mochida-san is...
- My college classmate.

115
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:07,080
And Shido-san is my client.

116
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:08,750
Huh?

117
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:10,300
Then what about you and Shido-san?

118
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:11,820
We work at the same company.

119
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:14,940
- What!
- You should've noticed from the business cards.

120
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:18,040
No, I get so many cards,
I don't pay attention.

121
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,600
- Wow, it's such a small world.
- Right?

122
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:24,090
Yotsuya and I lived in
the same dorm in college.

123
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,519
We hung out all the time.

124
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,750
Oh, I see.

125
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,290
We had Shido-san handle
our winery's wine recently.

126
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,360
The feedback was amazing.

127
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,970
Not at all... I was still
a rookie back then.

128
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,630
I caused you a lot of trouble.

129
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,269
No, no. Speaking of which,

130
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,930
I was a rookie back then too.

131
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,360
Even so,

132
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:44,849
- He's our company's ace salesman now.
- Hey, don't act like we're close.

133
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:45,760
Shut up.

134
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:48,169
- Huh, that's weird.
- Why are you like this?

135
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:49,450
Hey, what's your problem?

136
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:52,970
Could Shido-san be...

137
00:06:54,410 --> 00:06:57,280
the rival Yotsuya
mentioned from high school?

138
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:01,060
Huh? Yotsuya talked about me...?

139
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,520
Yes.

140
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:03,900
He said you were smart,

141
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:05,940
got good grades,

142
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,340
but were a bit pushy,

143
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:10,600
and a very competitive rival.

144
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,070
That's what I heard.

145
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,420
Oh, that's Tanaka-san.

146
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:17,240
Tanaka-san!

147
00:07:17,290 --> 00:07:18,870
Oh, he ran away...

148
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,240
Sorry.

149
00:07:20,530 --> 00:07:21,530
Did I say too much?

150
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:22,400
Not at all.

151
00:07:22,401 --> 00:07:24,310
I didn't think he'd tell
Mochida-san so much.

152
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,110
I'm sorry about that.

153
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:27,930
No, no, it actually makes
you seem more approachable.

154
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:30,089
Because you're always so perfect at work.

155
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:31,670
No, that's not true.

156
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,520
But I never imagined

157
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,769
the person I heard
about so often in college

158
00:07:35,770 --> 00:07:37,070
would be Shido-san.

159
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:38,860
That guy...

160
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,560
Did he say anything else weird?

161
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:41,630
Of course not.

162
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:44,140
He said you were a great rival.

163
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,709
But it's still hard to imagine.

164
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:50,710
Huh?

165
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,500
No, you two don't look like

166
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:54,840
the type to compete over anything.

167
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:57,160
It's surprising to hear you're rivals.

168
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:58,510
Is it?

169
00:07:58,820 --> 00:07:59,820
Yeah.

170
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:02,480
Yotsuya has always been a pacifist.

171
00:08:02,910 --> 00:08:03,910
And,

172
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,040
he was always popular with the girls.

173
00:08:09,470 --> 00:08:11,990
- Are you Yotsuya-san?
- Yes...

174
00:08:12,290 --> 00:08:13,920
Nice to meet you.

175
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:15,830
But looking at you now,

176
00:08:15,831 --> 00:08:18,674
I think I can kind of
understand why you're rivals

177
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:22,070
Mochida-san,

178
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:23,750
the director is looking for you.

179
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:26,310
Oh, right.

180
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,060
Sorry, Shido-san.

181
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:29,460
Enjoy the party tonight.

182
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:31,450
- Okay, thanks.
- Excuse me.

183
00:08:33,310 --> 00:08:34,230
Um...

184
00:08:34,231 --> 00:08:36,729
You're Shido-san from Blaze Link, right?

185
00:08:36,730 --> 00:08:38,860
Yes, I'm Shido from Sales Division 2.

186
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,090
I've heard about you from Mochida-san.

187
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:43,069
I've been wanting to talk to you.

188
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:44,220
I'd love to.

189
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:48,079
I really love the wine ad
you did for our company.

190
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,860
Oh, thank you so much.

191
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:50,539
Even though I work at a wine company,

192
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:52,480
I don't know anything about wine.

193
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:55,329
But that ad, from the perspective
of someone who doesn't know wine,

194
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:56,570
really resonated with me.

195
00:08:57,130 --> 00:08:57,820
Before that,

196
00:08:57,821 --> 00:09:01,080
wine always felt like something
only experts could talk about...

197
00:09:14,850 --> 00:09:17,590
Yotsuya and I lived in
the same dorm in college.

198
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:19,040
We hung out all the time.

199
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:24,880
Yotsuya has always been a pacifist.

200
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:26,430
And,

201
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:28,470
he was always popular with the girls.

202
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,500
So, I'm really happy.

203
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,500
Shido-san?

204
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:37,400
- Oh, yes.
- Are you alright?

205
00:09:37,830 --> 00:09:39,820
Oh, sorry. I was just zoning out.

206
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:42,030
I'll take my leave for now.

207
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:44,370
I hope we can talk again sometime.

208
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,310
- Definitely.
- Same here.

209
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:47,580
I'd love that.

210
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:58,770
Hey.

211
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:04,920
That girl you were talking
to earlier is pretty cute.

212
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:10,240
For a high-end company like this,

213
00:10:10,730 --> 00:10:13,220
the women at these parties are top-tier.

214
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,520
The one you were chatting
with was quite a looker.

215
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:21,860
Oh, you saw that?

216
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,060
Yeah.

217
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:29,850
She even asked if I
wanted to grab a drink later.

218
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,260
She's bolder than she looks.

219
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,120
Are you going?

220
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,360
Hmm?

221
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:43,580
I'm still thinking about it.

222
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:45,919
If you tell me not to go...

223
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:46,920
Don't go.

224
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:49,390
Hmm?

225
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:53,490
I said don't go...

226
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:56,083
What?

227
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:57,370
Are you jealous?

228
00:11:03,690 --> 00:11:04,790
Is it wrong to be?

229
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:10,200
Didn't I tell you that you're only
allowed to have eyes for me?

230
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:33,820
Do you really think I'll just let
you push me around forever?

231
00:11:38,620 --> 00:11:40,040
Don't talk nonsense...

232
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,550
You're clearly reacting to me.

233
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:43,530
Don't be dumb.

234
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:46,530
Wasn't it you who told me to
loosen up and enjoy myself?

235
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:49,750
What are you going to do?

236
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:51,980
Aren't those girls waiting for you?

237
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,530
You should probably get going.

238
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,230
I'm not going.

239
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:47,610
Wait.

240
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:49,070
What are you doing?

241
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,490
I haven't showered yet.

242
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,620
I'm not doing that with you.

243
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,320
Huh?

244
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:57,780
You...

245
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,100
This is your first time
with a man, isn't it?

246
00:13:01,146 --> 00:13:03,626
I can't be held responsible if
you actually get hooked on men.

247
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,480
Aren't you the one who's scared?

248
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:09,230
Scared that you'll fall for me.

249
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:13,566
- Here you go again, you arrogant jerk.
- I hit the nail on the head, didn't I?

250
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:15,990
You overthink everything.

251
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:56,709
- Stop it.
- What's your problem?

252
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:58,319
Even if you do that, I won't fall for you.

253
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,499
You're the one who provoked me.

254
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,020
Ugh, you're so annoying.

255
00:14:02,730 --> 00:14:04,040
I'm going to shower.

256
00:14:07,499 --> 00:14:09,549
What the hell?

257
00:14:50,050 --> 00:14:55,620
I lost from the very beginning, didn't I...

258
00:15:04,990 --> 00:15:06,190
Let's eat.

259
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:09,170
Ryo.

260
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:12,240
I heard you didn't place
first in the entrance exam.

261
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:17,480
I'm not saying you didn't work hard.

262
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:20,660
But you need to step it up
and make up for it from now on.

263
00:15:24,710 --> 00:15:25,710
Yes.

264
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:27,460
I'm sorry.

265
00:15:29,090 --> 00:15:30,930
I'm looking forward to
seeing what you can do.

266
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:39,570
So you're Shido-kun, the
one who took first place?

267
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,060
I'm Yotsuya. Nice to meet you.

268
00:15:49,688 --> 00:15:53,034
[Freshman First Semester Midterm
Exam Grades: Ryo 1st, Zen 2nd]

269
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:57,020
You're surprisingly competitive.

270
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:00,730
Huh?

271
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:08,070
I'll definitely beat you next time.

272
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:10,240
Is Shido-kun okay?

273
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:13,089
Oh, he's fine. It seems
like just mild anemia.

274
00:16:13,090 --> 00:16:14,139
I sent him home early to rest.

275
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:17,030
He's been looking unsteady
since this morning. It's worrying.

276
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,909
He's been burying himself in his studies.

277
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:20,970
He hasn't been sleeping much lately.

278
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,150
I thought so.

279
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:25,999
Is it because his brother
is so accomplished?

280
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,690
Ah, you mean Shido Rei?

281
00:16:28,380 --> 00:16:31,550
I told him not to push himself
so hard, but he wouldn't listen.

282
00:16:31,940 --> 00:16:34,240
Maybe he's under that kind of pressure.

283
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:55,360
Hey.

284
00:16:58,450 --> 00:16:59,910
What are you doing?

285
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:07,980
What?

286
00:17:09,220 --> 00:17:11,210
At first, I always thought...

287
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:12,509
that even without trying that hard,

288
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:13,870
you could do everything perfectly.

289
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:17,359
I thought you were just a
naturally gifted, annoying guy.

290
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,510
That's pretty rude, don't you think?

291
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:21,420
But,

292
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:24,860
I was wrong.

293
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:30,060
That arrogant pride of yours,

294
00:17:30,810 --> 00:17:32,050
and that confidence...

295
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:36,031
I realized that they stem from
an incredible amount of hard work.

296
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:44,100
I have a new respect for you.

297
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,540
Is that so? That's nice to hear.

298
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,720
You're annoying. Can you leave?

299
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:50,810
I'm genuinely complimenting you.

300
00:17:50,811 --> 00:17:52,060
Just take it like a man.

301
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:55,210
I don't feel like you're
complimenting me at all.

302
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:56,520
Huh?

303
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,320
Don't tell me...

304
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:01,740
Are you blushing?

305
00:18:02,589 --> 00:18:03,919
You're turning red.

306
00:18:03,971 --> 00:18:05,059
You're blushing, you're blushing~

307
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:06,260
Are you even listening to me?

308
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,300
Aren't you the same?

309
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:19,000
You can't reach first place
without putting in the work.

310
00:18:26,990 --> 00:18:28,090
I just...

311
00:18:28,296 --> 00:18:30,576
I was just trying to live up
to my parents' expectations.

312
00:18:31,723 --> 00:18:32,723
My father,

313
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:36,910
he's always had this strange
obsession with being 'number one'...

314
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:41,700
While I suppose that can
be a form of motivation,

315
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:46,900
it's probably not very constructive.

316
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:50,600
If you're going to put
in the effort anyway,

317
00:18:50,790 --> 00:18:52,270
instead of doing it for your parents,

318
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:54,189
why not work hard to be my rival?

319
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:55,510
Wouldn't that be more meaningful?

320
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:04,010
Even if you meet your
parents' expectations,

321
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,720
they might not necessarily meet yours.

322
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:16,580
Well, though you're not even
qualified to be my rival yet.

323
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,970
You talk too much.

324
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,410
You idiot.

325
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:24,069
- I will definitely surpass you.
- That's impossible.

326
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:25,080
You can't do it.

327
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,360
I like you...

328
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:40,500
What was that?

329
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:42,210
I thought you'd left.

330
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,430
So you still want to compete with me?

331
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:50,420
Since you don't know how to win me over,

332
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:53,160
you thought you'd just try seducing me?

333
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,140
That's a pretty cheap trick.

334
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:57,290
Even if it's cheap,

335
00:19:57,470 --> 00:19:59,120
it's my winning move.

336
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:00,699
I don't mind starting with the physical...

337
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,710
I...

338
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:04,650
I want you from the bottom of my heart.

339
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:07,570
Huh?

340
00:20:11,930 --> 00:20:13,480
Oh... never mind...

341
00:20:20,130 --> 00:20:21,230
You...

342
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,230
You should learn a little more,

343
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,040
about how to win someone
over besides just using your body.

344
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:30,110
You're selling yourself too cheap.

345
00:20:32,340 --> 00:20:33,340
Aren't you the same?

346
00:20:33,990 --> 00:20:35,750
All you ever do is tell
me I'm good-looking.

347
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:37,690
That's because I genuinely think you are.

348
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:39,170
And,

349
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:41,650
I love seeing how you're not
used to being complimented,

350
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:44,040
but you still get all shy about it.

351
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,920
What else?

352
00:20:51,310 --> 00:20:52,310
Huh?

353
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:55,850
Since you're so confident,

354
00:20:57,650 --> 00:21:00,600
try saying something else to seduce me.

355
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,020
Is your heart racing?

356
00:21:15,030 --> 00:21:16,130
As if.

357
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:21,110
Zen, you...

358
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:25,410
You never say sweet things to me.

359
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:30,080
But that actually makes me
feel like you're being sincere.

360
00:21:31,610 --> 00:21:32,610
It makes me happy.

361
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:39,920
Zen...

362
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:44,260
That arrogant, confident side of yours...

363
00:21:45,890 --> 00:21:48,470
I know how much effort
you put in behind the scenes.

364
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,250
That's why I respect you.

365
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:00,740
Do you remember?

366
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:03,880
What you said to me back then?

367
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:10,540
Instead of living up to
your parents' expectations,

368
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,100
why not work hard to keep being my rival?

369
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,700
That's more constructive.

370
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:18,700
Ah...

371
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:21,460
From then until now,

372
00:22:23,020 --> 00:22:25,010
you've always been my motivation.

373
00:22:25,630 --> 00:22:27,510
You're the reason I've
been able to keep going.

374
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:34,360
I couldn't say it back then,

375
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,000
but thank you.

376
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,420
That was only because...

377
00:22:43,220 --> 00:22:44,580
I felt like you were just like me,

378
00:22:44,890 --> 00:22:47,490
suffering from pointless
feelings of inferiority.

379
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:52,480
Because I've always felt
inferior to my brother too.

380
00:22:53,260 --> 00:22:54,260
Yeah.

381
00:22:55,260 --> 00:22:56,260
I know.

382
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,500
So,

383
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,120
I also...

384
00:23:02,810 --> 00:23:05,160
Um... thank you.

385
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,720
Huh?

386
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:13,080
The reason I can be this confident now,

387
00:23:13,870 --> 00:23:16,110
is because you taught me,
someone so full of self-doubt,

388
00:23:16,690 --> 00:23:18,420
about all these different emotions.

389
00:23:20,210 --> 00:23:21,410
Maybe it's because of you,

390
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:23,430
that I've become who I am.

391
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,390
- Hey.
- I won't do anything.

392
00:23:43,710 --> 00:23:45,040
I won't do anything...

393
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:48,950
Just let me hold you
like this for a while...

394
00:23:54,170 --> 00:23:55,750
After high school,

395
00:23:58,130 --> 00:24:00,210
I thought I'd never see you again.

396
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:04,210
So...

397
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:10,550
when we started at the same
company, I was so happy.

398
00:24:18,830 --> 00:24:19,830
So...

399
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:24,490
I never want to let you go again.

400
00:24:30,370 --> 00:24:32,260
Zen, to me...

401
00:24:36,970 --> 00:24:38,990
you've always been someone special.

402
00:26:00,670 --> 00:26:02,459
(Next Episode Preview)
I never expected Kiritani-san to show up.

403
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:06,400
(Episode 4: Are you the devil?!) I've been looking
for a chance to have a real talk with Shido-san.

404
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:08,350
- No, no, no.
- No, no, no.

405
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,339
You two are quite famous, you know.

406
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:11,999
Known as the rising stars
of Division 1 and Division 2.

407
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,100
Don't say that.

408
00:26:13,670 --> 00:26:15,520
He really is quite capable.

409
00:26:15,750 --> 00:26:18,680
Are you two just singing each
other's praises behind your backs?

410
00:26:19,290 --> 00:26:20,620
At the end of the day, I also...

411
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:24,050
want to be a rival worthy of you.

412
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:25,530
Kiritani-san.

413
00:26:26,930 --> 00:26:27,930
Um...
